"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-07-paris-2024-olympics-amusan-targets-womens-100m-hurdles-gold\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Tobi Amusan has set her sights on winning gold in the women's 100m hurdles at the Paris 2024 Olympic Games.  The world record holder raced into the semi-finals of the event on Wednesday morning.  Amusan won heat 1, crossing the line with a time of 12.49s.  The 27-year-old failed to make it to the podium three years ago in Tokyo.  She is however determined to claim the ultimate prize this time around.  \\\"       ,    18/19,                  ,    , '  n,\\\" Amusan told Making of Champions.  The Commonwealth and African champion will compete in the semi-final on Thursday.  Thiago Silva reacts as Brazilian Endrick picks Bellingham over Neymar  EPL: Ridiculous - Liverpool legend slams Andre Onana over message to Man Utd fans  2025 World Championships: Amusan credits 'God' for silver medal success  Amusan confirms for Diamond League season opener  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's dismal performance worries enthusiasts  Paris 2024 Olympics: D'Tigress' Wakama wins Best Coach award  Paris 2024 Olympics: Brume vows to  bounce back from disappointing outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Sports Minister apologises to Nigerians after disastrous outing  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"